Even further off-topic, I really like the succinctness of the former in CoffeeScript:<p><pre><code>  $(function () {
      $('#index').append($('article p:first-child'));
  });
</code></pre>
becomes:<p><pre><code>  $ -> $('#index').append $('article p:first-child')
</code></pre>
Not exactly noob-friendly, but very concise.
